article.headline: Montana State 87, Quinnipiac 75
article.story: MIAMI (AP) -- Danny Faaborg scored 19 points and five Montana State players finished in double figures to help the Bobcats beat Quinnipiac 87-75 in the opening round of the FIU Tip-Off Tournament on Friday. Faaborg was 5-of-6 from 3-point range for Montana State (1-0), which will play in Sunday's championship game against Howard, a 67-55 winner over Florida International in the other first-round game. Jason Erickson had 15, Matt Towsley scored 11 and P.J. Oswley and Calvin Ento each scored 10 for Montana State, which shot 63.6 percent in the first half and built a 50-29 lead at the break. Ento added a game-high 12 rebounds for the winners. Rob Monroe scored a game-high 23 points for Quinnipiac (0-1), which also got 17 points from Kason Mims. C.J. Vick added 10 for Quinnipiac, which missed 11 of its 20 free throws.
